Convergent Technologies Incsaid it has reached an agreement in principle to buy OakleafCorp, which supplies finance, insurance and leasing computersto auto dealers.    The transaction will involve an exchange of Oakleaf stockfor cash and debt and is subject to a definitive agreement, thecompanys said. No other terms were disclosed.    Oakleaf had 1986 sales of about 26 mln dlrs. Reuter&#3;